args:
The party wrests the Jin Gu Er back from
Qitian Dasheng and returns Wu Kong to his
senses. However, he is so enthralled by the
power of the relic that he is manipulated into
reclaiming it once again. The party then sets
off in the hopes of saving him for good.
We made it back. Is everyone all right?\nWhat about Wu Kong?
Looks like he's back to normal!\n...Or as normal as this guy gets.
Wait. I'm remembering now.\nI used the Jin Gu Er and...
Are you all right, Wu Kong?\nYou are not injured or feeling unwell?
No, I actually feel pretty good.
Listen, master. I'm REALLY sorry abou—
No, Wu Kong—I am the one who is sorry.\nResponsibility for this incident falls upon\nmy own failings alone.

What the heck are you talking about?!
I'M the giant doofus who decided to
start fiddling around with mystic stuff
that's way outta my league.
Yet it was my own failings as a teacher\nthat set you down your path.
As one who ought be guiding you,\nit is shameful—and I deeply regret it.\nI beg your forgiveness.
Master, I... This is so weird...

Enough. You must rest now. The power of
the relic put terrific strain on your body,
and we cannot be certain its effects do
not yet linger in some unknown fashion.
A-all right, master. I'll go rest.
The heck was THAT?! I thought she was\ngonna chew him out until he was sobbing\nin the fetal position.
Trust me, Notte—this is way worse.
Yeah. For the kid, getting a verbal\nbeatdown would've felt better.

The whole reason Wu Kong took the
Jin Gu Er in the first place was to gain
his teacher's acknowledgment of his
own expertise.
Which shows precisely what a figure\nXuan Zang is in his life.
It would be terrible to have someone you\nrespect be so sad about your actions.
I hope it doesn't impact our journey\nwhen we set out tomorrow.

*yawn* Man, I am bushed! Feels like we
walked a hundred miles and then some.
These Qilin really know how to build
their villages in the damn sticks.

Also, I gotta say, sleepin' outdoors is
startin' to take it outta me. Never used
to be a problem, back in my mercenary
days...
Sounds like the years are catchin'\nup to you.
Cork yer pie hole, chump! I ain't... Huh?
That kid again? The hell's his deal?
Uh, guys? Doesn't he seem a little...off?
Yeah, he ain't right for sure.\n'Course, he ain't never been, so...
Wu Kong? Heeey, Wu Kong!\nWhat's going on, buddy?
...Still awake, Xuan Zang? If you don't\nget some sleep, you'll likely be in for\na pretty rough day tomorrow.
Are you still worried about Wu Kong?
Mmm. I'd thought my concern to be\nbetter hidden than this. How shameful.
I'm not sure it'll make you feel any better,\nbut if you want to talk, I'm here.

In truth, I am still rather young and
untested in the world of sealers—
and honestly in no position to be
taking on a student of my own.
But the reason I insisted on training him\nis because I killed his parents.
A Qilin relic I ought to have sealed went\nout of control, killing them in the process.
I had no idea. I'm so sorry.
That day, I swore to watch over Wu Kong.\nBoth as his master, and as a kind of...\nWell, a foster parent, I suppose.
But now I am wondering if that was\na terrible miscalculation.
As a teacher, I am overjoyed at Wu Kong's\ngrowth. The boy possesses a rare talent\nfor the art of sealing.
But as a parent...I don't want him taking\non such a dangerous role!
Because of my hesitance, he has started\nto lose patience with the entire process.\nThis makes me a failure as a teacher.
Listen, Xuan Zang. This might just be\nmy opinion, but you're—
{player_name}! We got trouble!\nAnd not the fun kind!
Who... Who am I?\nAm I... Wu Kong...?
Wu Kong, you must fight this!
What's going on here, Xuan Zang?!\nWhy did he take the Jin Gu Er again?!
Wu Kong did not seek out the relic.\nRather, I fear the relic sought out HIM.
Once one has been possessed by a relic\nof the Qilin, it is no simple task for them\nto be freed from its thrall.
The connection between Wu Kong and the\nJin Gu Er was not severed when last we\nstruggled with it.
If only I could have controlled the relic's\npower, this would never have happened.
Oh, dang! Wu Kong's all ripped\nand evil-looking again!
How many times will I need to repeat it?\nMy name is not Wu Kong! It is...
Indeed, I am the great Qitian Dasheng!
And after the utter fool you made of me,\nI will slaughter all of you where you\nstand. I will slaugh...slau... Urrgh...
Bah, forget it! I'm more inclined to inflict\nmy rage elsewhere.
No, I'm fine. How about you guys?
Yeah, I got all my bits and pieces intact.\nStill we would've been in big trouble\nif Wu Kong didn't warn us away.
What the heck happened to him?!
If he has been completely consumed by\nthe power of the Jin Gu Er, we may not\nbe able to return him to normal.
There's still hope. He hesitated earlier\nwhen he was about to attack us, right?
That must be because he was\nresisting the relic's influence.
If that is true, then perhaps we do\nhave a faint sliver of hope.
A faint sliver is all I need!
Then let us get after him.
Leave it to me to find him, Xuan Zang.\nI will not possibly miss a presence\nas powerful as the Jin Gu Er.
Come on, everyone.\nWe've got a friend to save!
